text:
Charlie Kirk often said that when you stop talking with people you disagree with, that’s when violence happens.

There is no place for political violence in our society, and we should carry on Charlie’s mission of engaging in open debate in a free society. https://t.co/haaHNcCw9Y

I met with leaders from @kscorn and the @farmcredit to discuss the strong agriculture wins in the Working Families Tax Cuts bill, including historic investments into trade promotion programs like MAP and FMD, bolstering crop insurance, and updating reference prices. Now, Congress needs to pass Farm Bill 2.0 to ensure that producers have the certainty they need to plan for the future. Thank you both for the productive meetings.

Unfortunately, too many in Washington would rather see President Trump fail than work together to keep the government functioning and funded responsibly. It's time to stop the political grandstanding and do what's best for the country. https://t.co/I9A7O1lvpW

When terrorists attacked our country on 9/11, they didn’t see red states or blue states—they saw Americans. We should never let political divisions blind us to the fact that we are one nation, united under God.

When we lose sight of seeing the humanity in our fellow Americans who vote differently than us, we are feeding into the very thing our adversaries want– to destroy us from within.

We are better than this.

Every parent should have access to the classroom that best meets the educational needs of their children.

I had the opportunity to speak with members of @ACSIUSA during their trip to Washington about the importance of nationwide school choice initiatives and the hard work ACSI is doing to promote educational freedom.

I’m grateful for the work Christian educators do every day to serve students and strengthen communities. Thanks for having me!

.@HouseGOP embraced commonsense, pro-growth policies to deliver real wins for Kansas agriculture:

➡️ Expanded crop insurance
➡️ Updated reference prices
➡️ Reduced taxes on family farms

But now we must pass a full Farm Bill that provides further certainty and resources our agricultural community counts on to feed, fuel, and clothe the world.

America’s farmers and livestock producers deserve sound policies that strengthen our food supply, grow our rural economies, and reflect the changing nature of production agriculture. I sat down with @MeatInstitute and the Kansas Pork Association in Washington last week to discuss the labor shortages facing meat processors, misguided regulatory efforts like Prop 12, and the need for common-sense, science-based nutrition guidelines. Thanks for the meeting.

Every instance of fraud or overpayment in the SNAP program is money taken from vulnerable families in our state who rely on this assistance to meet their nutritional needs. Kansans deserve a system that protects taxpayer dollars and serves the people it was designed to help.

@RepRonEstes and I sent a letter to Governor Kelly to urge her to work with @USDA to strengthen SNAP instead of allowing millions of Kansans’ tax dollars to be wasted and abused.

Grain handlers, feed processors, and ag suppliers are vital to Kansas' farm economy. I had the opportunity to speak with the @NGFA in Washington this week to share updates on our legislative priorities, including the ag wins we secured in July and the ongoing progress toward passing Farm Bill 2.0. 

We had a productive discussion and I appreciated their thoughtful questions and continued commitment to feeding the world. Thanks for inviting me!

Pharmacy Benefit Managers have driven up costs and hurt patients for too long. I cosponsored the PBM Reform Act to increase transparency in the industry and ban abusive drug pricing.

This is a commonsense step to bring accountability to the prescription drug supply chain.

Energy producers and manufacturers play a critical role in powering our economy and strengthening American supply chains. I appreciated the opportunity to meet with @GrowthEnergy, who presented me with the Fueling Growth Award, and with the team at Viega, a Kansas-based plumbing manufacturer and global leader in press technology. We discussed the importance of year-round E15, fair implementation of the 45Z tax credit, and policies that help Kansas manufacturers remain competitive. Thanks for meeting with me!

We passed the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2026 — a critical investment in our national defense and the men and women who serve.

This legislation strengthens our military readiness, modernizes our defense capabilities, gives our troops a pay raise, and secures our border through permanent policy reforms.

No American should have to sacrifice access to quality health care because of their zip code.

As the representative of 60 primarily rural counties across the state of Kansas, I understand the unique challenge rural America faces in accessing quality health care. That’s why I introduced three pieces of legislation that remove these regulatory barriers and make necessary modernizations that bring rural health care to the 21st century. Health care cannot be a one-size-fits-all policy. 

These commonsense reforms better equip health care facilities and professionals to effectively meet the needs of the communities they serve.

When you pray with someone it’s hard to hate them. 
 
We can disagree with people without demonizing them. It is my prayer that our nation can come together, pray for healing, and disagree well without hating one another.
 
Thank you @BretBaier for having me on @SpecialReport’s Common Ground segment with @RepTomSuozzi. We cannot stop talking simply because we disagree.

It was great catching up with Kansans in Washington, DC last night at the annual Kansas State Society dinner.

And of course, it's always fun to have the opportunity to sing Home on the Range with the Kansas delegation. Thank you, Kansas State Society, for a wonderful evening!

September 11, 2001 is a day our nation will never forget.

We remember the 2,977 innocent lives lost, and honor the heroism of our first responders and the brave men and women in uniform who answered the call to serve in the aftermath. Their courage and sacrifice continue to inspire us 24 years later. #NeverForget
Please pray for Charlie Kirk and his family.

In July, @HouseGOP passed landmark legislation to support Kansas ag producers by increasing the farm safety net, lowering taxes across the board, and doubling funding to market access programs.

This was a win for Kansas agriculture, but we still need to pass a comprehensive, five-year Farm Bill that addresses the issues of today, not those of 2018.

I sat down with the Greater Topeka Chamber of Commerce in Washington this week to discuss the gems of the animal health corridor, workforce development, and growing the aviation industry in northeast Kansas. From the opening of Link Innovation Labs to the 190th Air Refueling Wing, Topeka is leading the way in high-impact sectors that matter to our national security and state economy. Thanks for the meeting!

The FAA currently employs 2,300 fewer Certified Professional Controllers than needed and continues to fall below its hiring and certification targets. The shortage has forced many controllers to work mandatory overtime, leading to fatigue and increasing the risk of errors.

Last night, we passed the Mental Health in Aviation Act of 2025, legislation I cosponsor with @RepPeteStauber, @RepCasten, and @RepRickLarsen, which ensures that we can prepare and effectively equip the next generation of capable, qualified air traffic controllers to protect the future safety of our skies and maintain the American gold standard of aviation.

In July, Congressional Republicans and @POTUS passed legislation to cut taxes for Americans of all income levels while eliminating taxes on tips, overtime, and social security.

After years of record inflation and government irresponsibility, Republicans are putting working-class Americans first. Promises made, promises kept.

Congressional Republicans and @POTUS have secured the border, cut taxes, and are restoring American strength at home and abroad.

Kansans are seeing the results of real leadership in Washington, DC. Promises made, promises kept. 🇺🇸🇺🇸

The week is off to a busy start here in Washington, DC. Yesterday, I introduced three rural health care bills that will modernize our Rural Health Clinics and ensure every American has equal access to quality care, no matter their zip code.

I also spoke on the House floor today to highlight the storied tradition of the Kansas State Fair. For more than a century, families have made the trip to Hutchinson every September to celebrate agriculture, spend time together, and showcase the very best of our state. While I’m sad I couldn’t stay longer, I’m looking forward to another week of supporting Kansas ag by fighting for conservative, commonsense policies in our nation’s capital.

Rural America trusted @POTUS and @HouseGOP to provide relief, & that’s just what we did. We put Kansas agriculture first by:

➡️Updating reference prices to reflect today’s ag economy
➡️Strengthening crop insurance for our farmers
➡️Doubling investments in trade promotion programs like MAP and FMD

These commonsense wins give Kansas farmers and ag producers the certainty they need to continue feeding, fueling, and clothing the world.

After four years of sky-high inflation and reckless government spending, @HouseGOP passed the largest tax cut for working- and middle-class families in decades.

I am proud that our pro-growth, pro-family legislation is helping Kansans keep more of their hard-earned money each month.

Our @HouseGOP majority & @POTUS put working and middle class families first by:

➡️Preventing the largest tax hike in decades
➡️Doubling the Child Tax Credit
➡️Expanding education savings accounts

This is what families in the Big First voted for. https://t.co/ASQ9GhbYQm

The Chinese Communist Party’s treatment of the Uyghur people is a grave violation of human rights.

The House passed the Uyghur Policy Act to stand with oppressed minority communities in China and ensure the United States leads with moral clarity on the world stage.

The start of fall means football across all levels has officially kicked off in Kansas!

Looking forward to a full weekend of high school football, as well as @Chiefs, @KStateFB, and @KU_Football games.

Great weekend to be a football fan. https://t.co/T5Z28Kp92a

Kansans rejected open border policies, foreign energy dependence, and radical federal overreach last November.

Instead, our state voted to put America First, and that is what @HouseGOP and @POTUS are doing. Promises made, promises kept.

Millions of family farms and small businesses will benefit from our pro-growth policies and working families tax cut. By making 199A deductions permanent and expanding the death tax exemption, we are keeping operations in the family and allowing more Kansans to pass on their life’s work to the next generation.

The House passed H.R. 747, the Stop Chinese Fentanyl Act, to hold China accountable for flooding our communities with deadly drugs.

Fentanyl is devastating families and taking thousands of American lives. This legislation is an important step to crack down on bad actors and protect our communities.

Our One Big Beautiful Bill makes the 2017 Trump tax cuts permanent, expands the farm safety net, and eliminates taxes on tips and overtime. 💰

Our bill delivers real relief for working families and rural America. Promises made, promises kept.

Strong communities are built on safety and economic opportunity. I had the chance to meet with the Ottawa County Sheriff’s Office and visit @GLHuyett in Minneapolis to discuss supporting law enforcement and growing manufacturing jobs across Kansas. Thanks for the meetings!

Access to quality health care is vital to our rural communities. I visited SunPorch in Smith Center—where I met Blondina Kuhlmann, who just celebrated her 100th birthday—and toured Graham County Hospital in Hill City to learn more about how providers are caring for Kansans across the Big First. Thank you for the meetings!

While traveling across the Big First, I visited the Kansas Veterans Cemetery in WaKeeney and the Cheyenne County Veterans Memorial to honor those who served our nation with courage and conviction.

With Fort Riley and the 1st Infantry Division—the oldest continuously serving division in the U.S. Army—in our district, Kansas has a proud military tradition. I’m deeply grateful for the generations of service members who have defended our freedoms and shaped our nation’s history.

Border security was the number one issue last November, and President Trump’s results speak for themselves.

Under @POTUS, we've seen record-low apprehensions at our southern border & the end of failed catch and release policies. 📉

This is what Kansans voted for.

The One Big Beautiful Bill invests in the future of agriculture by lowering taxes for producers and strengthening the farm safety net.

We still must pass a comprehensive, five-year Farm Bill that provides certainty for our producers, further invests in animal health research, and addresses the issues of today, not 2018.

Strong local banks and co-ops keep our businesses and our communities thriving. I visited Ellsworth Cooperative and Citizens State Bank during my time in Ellsworth to talk about supporting rural credit, expanding the agricultural workforce, and cutting red tape that makes it harder to do business in rural America. Thanks for having me!

Food security is national security.

A strong Farm Bill supports rural America, ensures stability at home, and keeps America fed, fueled, and clothed. 🧑‍🌾🚜🐮🌾

The Big First economy relies on our agricultural and energy producers to fuel our lives and feed our families. I visited @CentralValleyAg and the Lincoln Power Plant to talk about fertilizer production, farm input costs, and the importance of an all-of-the-above energy strategy that prioritizes reliability and affordability. Thank you for showing me around!

I spoke with @OfficialRFDTV about how growing up on a family farm and feedlot taught me the values of faith, family, hard work, and service, and how those same values guide my work in Congress today.
https://t.co/Wi68JMTwUl

Four years ago today, the Abbey Gate attack in Kabul took the lives of thirteen courageous U.S. service members.

We will never forget their sacrifice or the consequences of failed leadership. https://t.co/BRwRBAa1zP

America needs an all-of-the-above energy strategy that unleashes energy dominance, strengthens the nation’s energy supply, and powers our lives without relying on foreign energy.

It was great to join KIOGA at their annual convention to talk about how we can strengthen American energy production and support independent oil and gas producers who drive growth across Kansas.

Manufacturing plays a key role in rural economies across Kansas. 👷🏗️

I visited @OsborneInd and @StarSeedKS in Osborne to see firsthand how Kansas-made innovation is driving growth, creating jobs, and supporting our ag producers. Thanks for the conversations and for investing in rural America.

The One Big Beautiful Bill is the most pro-growth, pro-family legislation in a generation.

Our legislation protects family farms, cuts taxes on Americans of all income levels, and supports our ag producers as they feed, fuel, and clothe the world.

The Big First is the top wheat-producing district in the nation, and grain milling plays a key role in that supply chain. I met with ADM Milling Company in Abilene to talk about strengthening domestic food production and bolstering trade relationships for Kansas agriculture. Thanks for the tour!

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivers real wins for Kansas agriculture:

➡️ Expanded crop insurance
➡️ Updated reference prices
➡️ Decreased taxes on family farms 

But now we must pass a full Farm Bill that provides further certainty and includes the many “orphan programs” our producers count on to feed, fuel, and clothe the world.

Today, the United States is more secure than it has been in years. It turns out that common sense and enforcing the law work after all.

Thank you, @POTUS, for making America safe again. 

Promises made, promises kept. https://t.co/7Mk5sR2h8x

Rural health care and conservation are both essential for the Big First’s way of life. I stopped by Rice County District Hospital and met with the Rice County Conservation District in Lyons to discuss improving access to care and preserving the land we rely on. Thanks for meeting with me!

The strong, decisive leadership of @POTUS, @SecRollins, and @USDA continues to put the farmers, ranchers, and ag producers who feed, fuel, and clothe the world first. Investing in a domestic sterile fly facility is a critical step to stop the spread of New World Screwworm.

Thank you for standing with American ranchers and taking decisive action to protect American livestock. Promises made, promises kept.

Kansas farmers, ranchers, and agricultural producers have always been and always will be the original conservationists of the land. The District Court of West Texas’ ruling to remove the lesser prairie-chicken from the endangered and threatened species list honors their stewardship of the land and acknowledges the facts on the ground. 

This ruling is a win for Kansas agricultural and energy producers and a huge loss for radical climate activists and bureaucrats who have abused the Endangered Species Act for over a decade to hurt American agriculture and energy production.

I was honored to attend the 130th Field Artillery Brigade deployment ceremony in Manhattan, where I spoke with the courageous young men and women about their service to our nation and their upcoming deployment.

Thank you, Colonel Daniel Ball, commander of the Brigade, for your devotion to our country. As you all depart, I extend my heartfelt wishes for your safety, security, and continued success.
The One Big Beautiful Bill delivers long overdue certainty for Kansas ag producers who feed, fuel, and clothe the world. https://t.co/c06cdyHIpZ

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivers certainty for our farmers and ranchers so they can continue to feed, fuel, and clothe the world.

This is what Kansans voted for in November. https://t.co/raRg9IK2fP
https://t.co/MNWT4PoXdz

While I’m traveling across the Big First, my D.C. staff stopped by the Shop Kansas Farms booth at the Great American Farmers Market on the National Mall—part of the @america250 celebration.

Thank you to @SecRollins and everyone at @USDA who helped showcase and celebrate the hard work of our nation’s ag producers who feed, fuel, and clothe the world. I am proud to see Kansas farmers front and center.

Our One Big Beautiful Bill is delivering on @POTUS’ agenda for Kansas through historic tax cuts, a stronger ag safety net, and increased investment in aviation.

More from my conversation with Marc Jacobs:
https://t.co/crGKcndJAd

I was honored to speak at the rededication of Stan Herd’s mural in Dodge City—a powerful tribute to the history and resilience of western Kansas.

The mural captures the spirit of the settlers who built this region and the pride that still defines it today. Thank you to Stan and everyone who made this celebration possible.

The agricultural supply chain relies on timely & reliable delivery from production to consumption.

My Seasonal Agriculture CDL Modernization Act makes it easier for farm-service drivers to do their jobs and serve customers & consumers.

Thank you @AgRetailers  for your support.
The One Big Beautiful Bill codifies @POTUS’ border security actions by funding the border wall and investing in technology to eliminate human and drug trafficking. https://t.co/zLwml05GaP

The Big First is home to crown jewels of the animal health corridor.

Thanks to the OBBBA, we’re investing in science that helps prevent disease outbreaks before they happen and protects the future of American agriculture.
https://t.co/yLHGrtq6nP

The Big First is home to the crown jewels of animal health research, where world-renowned innovation strengthens our food supply and protects global food security. I met with the Farm Journal Foundation to discuss advancing ag research to prevent future disease outbreaks before they begin. Thanks for your commitment to the future of agriculture.

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivered for Kansas agriculture: stronger crop insurance, higher reference prices, more trade promotion funding, and key investments in animal health research.

More on how @HouseAgGOP is supporting farmers:
https://t.co/uujXCQ1EeM

In just six short months, President Trump has reversed four years of disastrous open border failures from the previous administration. In June, CBP saw historic low levels of illegal crossings and apprehensions at the border.

This is the law and order Kansans voted for. https://t.co/91TOr81BaG

My first job in Congress was serving as an intern for a member from Kansas. I understand full well just how impactful the experience can be.

This summer, I welcomed five exceptional interns to our Washington, D.C., office: Sage, Elizabeth, Walker, Nicholas, and Cadence. They have brought great talent to the team, and we’ve been lucky to have them with us over the past few months. Thanks for all your hard work this summer, and happy National Intern Day!

Rural America is the heartbeat of the country.

I joined @OfficialRFDTV’s Champions of Rural America to talk about the state of the farm economy, the threat of New World Screwworm, and why animal health research and prevention must be top priorities.
https://t.co/ySSWWu5QIt
67 years ago today, Kansas’ favorite son, President Dwight D. Eisenhower, established @NASA by signing the National Aeronautics and Space Act into law. https://t.co/ovfeY4chNy

The Big First is home to many of the crown jewels of animal health research, where cutting-edge research occurs every single day.

The OBBBA increased funding for animal health research to limit disease outbreaks before they begin and eliminate risks to our food supply chain. https://t.co/fbj45cqJCG

Advocating for Kansans with disabilities means supporting strong public policy and community-based services that provide the resources they need. I met with the @KS_DD_Council to talk about expanding access to care, strengthening ABLE accounts, and supporting families across the Big First. Thanks for meeting with me.

States have the right to govern affairs within their borders, but the impact of Prop 12 extends far beyond California. The proposition not only threatens the livelihoods of Kansas hog farmers but also sets a terrible precedent for interstate commerce.

@HouseAgGOP will not allow one state’s radical policies to dictate policy for ag producers across the country.

Born in Dodge City, National Beef provides quality beef that feeds people all across the world. We discussed innovation in beef grading, cattle markets, and ensuring fair competition across the beef sector during their recent visit to Washington, D.C.. Thank you, National Beef, for the quality protein and jobs you provide to Kansans across the Big First!

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivers the largest tax cut for working and middle-class families in American history while securing our southern border to keep Americans safe.

This is common-sense legislation that helps Kansans keep more of what they earn. https://t.co/bi53kgXV2D
https://t.co/mQbEi8xHYZ

No one fights harder for America’s farmers & ranchers than @POTUS.  

Thank you President Trump, @SecRollins, and @USTradeRep for your leadership. This is the art of the deal. Promises made, promises kept.

Our One Big Beautiful Bill delivers for Kansas farmers, ranchers, and rural communities:

➡️Increases and permanently extends the Small Business Deduction
➡️Expands crop insurance
➡️Strengthens the farm safety net
➡️Protects two million family farms from the death tax

🚨 In just six months, @POTUS has delivered:

✅ Largest tax cut for working and middle-class Americans in history
✅ Record border security
✅ Cooling inflation
✅ $9 billion cut in wasteful federal spending
✅ U.S. energy dominance
✅ No taxes on tips or overtime
✅ Stock market all-time highs
✅ Strengthened farm safety net

Promises made, promises kept.
Just like during his first term, our economy is thriving again under @POTUS

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivers the largest tax cut for middle- and working-class families in American history.

Our bill delivers for families who depend on tips, Social Security, or overtime pay to make ends meet. President Trump and @HouseGOP are fighting and delivering for working families.

Six months into his second term, it’s clear that President Trump has delivered for Kansans time and time again.

From secure borders to the largest tax relief for middle and working class families in American history, @POTUS is delivering on the mandate the country gave him.
https://t.co/E7QBYjB1DE

The economy is thriving under @POTUS:

✅Inflation cooling
✅Unemployment claims down
✅Housing starts and permits up
✅Retail sales & consumer confidence booming

https://t.co/WxWEINyE2b

Thank you, @POTUS, for continuing to get our country back on track.

Promises made, promises kept.

Military Families shouldn’t be forced to wait weeks for closure because of red tape.

I’m proud to cosponsor the Veteran Burial Timeliness and Death Certificate Accountability Act to ensure our nation’s heroes are laid to rest without unnecessary bureaucratic delays. This bill would require the VA to certify a veteran’s death within 48 hours of notification, allow local officials to step in if the deadline is missed, and direct the VA Secretary to report to Congress on delays.

https://t.co/E9oOqkvDxz

If @HouseGOP did not pass the One Big Beautiful bill, the average Kansan would pay an extra $2,200 per year in taxes to the federal government.

Thankfully, we did not let that happen, and we cut taxes on tips and overtime while we were at it.

That is what I call delivering for Kansans.

The One Big Beautiful Bill codifies President Trump’s priorities while lowering taxes, securing the border, and reducing federal waste, fraud, and abuse.

Promises made, promises kept. https://t.co/uXe62nYLur

Extreme heat is moving across the Big First over the next few days, with dangerous temperatures expected through midweek. Please take the proper precautions, stay hydrated, and check on your neighbors.
https://t.co/aS5aLKA6Vw

Soybeans are essential to Kansas agriculture and the economic activity of the Big First. I met with @KsSoybean to discuss conservation programs, biofuel production, and trade policies that protect farm income and expand market access. Thanks for all you do to feed and fuel the world!

As the number one sorghum-producing congressional district, residents of the Big First know the impact sorghum has on our economy. I appreciated meeting with @SorghumGrowers to talk about opportunities to strengthen export opportunities for sorghum producers and my priorities for the next iteration of the Farm Bill. Thanks for stopping by!

Corn producers in the Big First play a vital role in feeding and fueling the world. I met with @kscorn to discuss year-round E15, the importance of passing a five-year, comprehensive Farm Bill, and how we can strengthen the future of biofuels. Thanks for meeting with me! https://t.co/RY0ZKsG7vn

The defense funding passed by the House last week strengthens our national security, improves housing and care for service members, and invests in our military so they can keep America safe.

God bless America and God bless our troops.

Agribusiness drives our Kansas economy and helps feed, fuel, and clothe the world. I appreciated the chance to speak with the Kansas Grain and Feed Association, along with the 2025 class of Tomorrow’s Agribusiness Leaders, about their work strengthening the ag workforce and supporting rural communities. Thanks for all you do for our state!

The Big First District is home to crown jewels of the animal health corridor, where world-renowned research helps prevent disease outbreaks in our animals.

We cannot afford to put our food security at risk by not prioritizing adequate investments in our animal health research. I urge my colleagues in the House of Representatives to prioritize a five-year, comprehensive Farm Bill to get this right.

The Marysville @UnionPacific Depot once served as a gateway to the western U.S., bringing millions of Americans to visit our National Parks. Last week, I toured the Depot and got to hear more about their efforts to preserve this historic Kansas landmark.

Built in 1929, the Pacific Union Depot stands as a reminder of the generations of Kansans who helped connect our communities and power American commerce. Thanks for having me!

Want to stay up-to-date on my work representing you in Washington and across the Big First?

Sign up for my weekly newsletter at the link below!

https://t.co/4v5y5USH00

I met with members from Kansas Special Education Cooperative to talk about how we can better support students with disabilities in the Big First.

From early childhood through graduation, every student deserves the resources they need to reach their full potential. Thanks for the meeting!

The One Big Beautiful Bill supports an all-of-the-above energy strategy by rolling back Biden-era overregulations and unleashing American energy dominance.

Promises made, promises kept. https://t.co/UWy96Ux0og

From Fort Riley to the frontlines, our men and women in uniform deserve the resources they need as they put their lives on the line to defend our freedoms. 

I voted to advance the Fiscal Year 2026 defense appropriations bill to ensure our warfighters can effectively protect our nation.

The One Big Beautiful Bill delivered for our agricultural producers by strengthening the farm safety net, investing in animal research, and better positioning the U.S. to prevent disease outbreaks within our borders. https://t.co/0qNWI74ToQ

Agricultural retailers like @AGCOcorp are helping producers stay competitive by embracing innovative technology and precision solutions. I toured their Beloit facilities and heard more about how their work supports farmers across Kansas with the tools, inputs, and expertise they need to maximize yields and protect our natural resources. Their commitment to rural communities and forward-thinking agriculture is making a real impact across our state. Thanks for all you do!

Our state relies on a strong aviation sector to support our ag producers, provide good-paying jobs, and make sure our farmers, ranchers, and agricultural producers can deliver their products to global markets.

During our @TransportGOP hearing, I heard from @SecDuffy about the state of our aviation export markets.

Career and technical education is preparing the next generation of Kansas leaders with the skills they need to succeed. I visited Fort Hays State University’s North Central campus in Beloit to hear about their growing programs and the important partnerships they’ve built with local industries.

Thank you, Fort Hays, for serving students across the state of Kansas and for all you do to ensure the next generation of Kansans can lead well!

Skilled trades and precision manufacturing play a vital role in keeping America’s farms running and rural economies growing. I visited Herrs Machine Hydrostatics in Washington, Kansas, to hear about their work supporting agricultural producers with reliable parts, expert service, and skilled local jobs.

Thank you, Herrs Marchine, for all you do for Kansas agriculture.

The One Big Beautiful Bill made historic investments in rural America by updating reference prices, expanding crop insurance, and cutting taxes on family farms.

But Kansas producers still need a five-year, fiscally conservative Farm Bill that keeps American agriculture competitive.

America needs an all-of-the-above energy strategy that promotes American energy dominance, not Green New Deal policies that pick winners & losers.

I visited Bluestem Electric Cooperative in Clay Center to talk about rural energy, grid reliability, and how federal policy impacts electric co-ops in Kansas. Co-ops like Bluestem are vital in powering homes, farms, and businesses across the Big First. Thanks for showing me around!
UPDATE: My telephone town hall has been moved to 5:30 PM CT tonight. Hope to hear from you!

Yesterday, I chaired a hearing on strengthening the National Animal Health Laboratory Network. Investing in proactive animal disease prevention serves as the most cost-effective approach to protecting our food supply and ensuring we never depend on another country for our food. 

Food security is national security and we cannot afford to put our food supply chain at risk.

June’s inflation report confirms what Americans are already feeling: prices are finally stabilizing.

Under President Trump, core inflation is beating expectations, wages are rising, and everyday costs are coming down. This is the leadership Kansans voted for.

Kansas farm cooperatives do more than store and ship grain— they help entire communities thrive. I stopped in at Randall Farmers Cooperative Union in Jewell to hear about this year’s harvest and talk about how we can strengthen agriculture across the Big First. Thank you for having me!

The One Big Beautiful Bill is now the law of the land. That means:

✅ Lower taxes for working families
✅ A stronger farm safety net
✅ American energy dominance
✅ The largest border security investment in U.S. history

This is what the Big First voted for in November.

I’ll be hosting a telephone town hall tonight to hear directly from Kansans in the Big First District. You can join the livestream and submit your questions at 6:30 PM CT at the link below. I hope you’ll tune in and be part of the conversation.

https://t.co/t2IQDSKuag

As Chair of the Livestock, Dairy, and Poultry Subcommittee, I understand the risk that New World Screwworm poses to the American cattle industry.

Yesterday’s hearing underscored the importance of positioning the United States to focus on disease prevention rather than outbreak control and emphasized how that posture strengthens our food security and supply chain.

I applaud the decisive and proactive actions @SecRollins and @POTUS are taking to keep the New World Screwworm out of our country.

Under @POTUS we have the most secure border our nation has ever recorded. 

This is exactly what Kansans voted for in November. Promises made, promises kept.

Natural gas access is essential for powering homes, businesses, and ag operations across rural Kansas. I met with Rural Gas, Inc. in Belleville to discuss the challenges facing natural gas providers and the importance of having sound federal energy policy to help them solve these challenges.

Rural America depends on providers like Rural Gas to keep its communities fueled and running. Thanks for having me!

It was great to stop by the Jewell County Fair last week to celebrate the values that make Kansas great and see so many friendly faces and impressive livestock. Thanks to everyone who helps make the fair a success year after year, and thanks for a fun visit! https://t.co/HA9gyClAPQ

Community colleges like Cloud County Community College are preparing the next generation of Kansas leaders, workers, and innovators for the future.
